    "To address this issue, we adopt self-attention graph pooling (SAGPooling) [32] as the final readout function.",
    "Specifically, SAGPooling incorporates hierarchical pooling and self-attention mechanisms to distinguish between nodes that should be removed and retained, considering both the molecule's atomic features and topological structure features, whose specific output size (7) and parameters for the SAGPooling are recorded in Table 2.",
    "For each GAT layer l, the final readout function is as follows:e ij = LeakytextReLU W h i � W h j, j ∈ N i, (8) α ij = softmax e ij.",
    "(9) h ′ i =σ   � j∈N i α ij W h j  ,(10) h′ i = k=1 K � σ   � j∈N i α ij k W k h j  .where A is the adjacency matrix, X (l) is the embeddings of all nodes in the l th layer's, WSAG ∈ R d(l)×1 are l th layer's trainable matrix, d is the input dimension of node-level features.",
    "Drug molecule sequence feature extractionTable 3 summarises the corresponding parameters of the model components used in the extraction of sequence information for individual drugs and the transformation of the feature dimensions."
